cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the capacity-achieving properties of sparse superposition codes and derives a large deviation bound on the probability of decoding error, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the computational efficiency of the decoding technique used for sparse superposition codes, which is an important aspect of computational complexity. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Sparse superposition codes have applications in network coding and communication over networks, which are topics covered in the social and information networks sub-category. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Sparse superposition codes have applications in image and video compression, which are topics covered in the multimedia sub-category. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Sparse superposition codes have applications in wireless communication and network coding, which are topics covered in the networking and internet architecture sub-category.
